BUG-REPORTING
-------------

If you found a bug in RNTrack, you may post information about it in the
Fidonet echo area "RU.FTRACK" (Russian), also you may post information
in the issues on the RNTrack project page on GitHub
(https://github.com/dukelsky/rntrack/issues), or you may send a message
to a maintainer via Fidonet netmail or internet email.

Please try to reproduce the bug before contacting the authors.

Things to do when you encounter a bug:

If RNTrack created a core dump:
- start `gdb` with
   gdb rntrack core
- type `where`
   where
- try to get all information out of the core file that could be interesting
  for the maintainer (this is for the people familiar with programming in C).

Send the following things:
- an extensive description of the situation where the bug happened.
- the RNTrack version
- the SMAPI version
- your config files
- all SMALL files RNTrack was using when the bug happened
  (pkt's/msg's/SQUISH's or JAM's). Please send me complete msg base only in
  the case when you could not reproduce the problem with a small one.
- a short description of what system you are using.
  (OS - Distribution - compiler - etc. I do NOT need to know what kind of
  monitor you use :-)

